üìñ The Story of Misbourne

The Misbourne flows through the Thames & S. Chilterns catchment, where our eDNA survey sampled 10 sites along its length. Analysis of water samples revealed a rich invertebrate community with 7,398 distinct genetic sequences (ESVs) representing 755 identified species and 262 families.

Compared to other chalk streams surveyed, the Misbourne shows one of the most biodiverse rivers in the study, ranking #2 of 10. The river supports 17 families of mayflies, stoneflies, and caddisflies (EPT) - key indicators of water quality.

Notable findings include the detection of conservation priority species (Water vole, Water shrew) and invasive species requiring management attention.
